# {{project_name}}

## Repo rules (enforced by reassure)

This repo uses [operation-reassurance](https://github.com/avarga1/operation-reassurance)
to enforce structural rules. A PreToolUse hook is active — **file writes that violate
error-severity rules will be blocked automatically.**

### Before writing any file

Call the `check_repo_rules` MCP tool with the proposed path and content.
Resolve all `error` violations before proceeding. `warning` violations should be
fixed before merging but will not block the write.

### Key rules for this stack

| Rule | Severity | What it catches |
|------|----------|-----------------|
| no-print-in-prod | error | `print()` in lib/ |
| no-inline-mock-data | error | MockData/FakeData/testUser in prod |
| no-hardcoded-urls | error | Inline http/https strings |
| no-localhost | error | localhost/127.0.0.1 in prod |
| no-hardcoded-colors | warning | `Colors.red`, `Color(0x…)` |
| no-inline-text-style | warning | `TextStyle(fontSize:…)` |
| no-imperative-navigation | warning | `Navigator.push` |
| no-media-query-size | warning | `MediaQuery.of(context).size` |
| no-raw-border-radius | warning | `BorderRadius.circular(…)` |
| no-raw-edge-insets | warning | `EdgeInsets.symmetric(…)` |
| no-raw-sized-box-spacing | warning | `SizedBox(height:…)` |

Run `reassure .` for a full repo health report.
